# Frontend environment variables.
#
# Local dev: copy to .env.local and fill in. Vite picks it up automatically.
# Netlify prod: set these in
#   Site settings -> Environment variables -> Add a variable
# (Vite bakes VITE_* vars into the bundle at build time, so you must
# redeploy after changing them.)
#
# Leave VITE_API_URL empty to use the Vite dev proxy (default).
# Set it to your Render backend URL in production, e.g.
#   VITE_API_URL=https://studysync-api.onrender.com

# VITE_API_URL=https://studysync-api.onrender.com
